cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new methodology for evaluating contextual bandit algorithms for online recommendation systems. It also involves empirical results on a large-scale dataset, which is a common characteristic of papers in this sub-category. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as news article recommendation is a common application in this field. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as contextual bandit algorithms are a type of reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of AI. 

It may also fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as it involves the evaluation of algorithms for a specific application domain (news article recommendation). 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the evaluation of recommendation algorithms is closely related to user experience and interaction with the system.
